Package: MLfused
Title: Multinomial Logistic Regression with Empirical-Likelihood Data Fusion
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chi-Shian", "Dai", email = "47463697+chichiihc@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Jun", "Shao", email = "shao@stat.wisc.edu", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Fits multinomial logistic regression models that incorporate
    external machine-learning predictions via empirical-likelihood (EL)
    moment constraints, as proposed by Dai and Shao (2025). Implements
    Newton-step optimization with analytic gradient and Hessian, sandwich
    and bootstrap standard error estimators, and flexible constraint basis
    construction (raw covariates or natural splines).
